<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-21T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-21T19:00:00-05:00" n="831" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d831">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">800.6176/9–2044: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-21T20:00:00-04:00">September 21,
                                1944—8 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>7704. For Bliss from Haley. Department agrees to press release changes
                        suggested in Embassy’s 7776 of September 20 including change in final
                        paragraph. Release to be issued here 7:30 p.m. Friday, September 22
                        (equivalent to your 00:30 Saturday, September 23).<note n="46" xml:id="d831fn46">For text of press release issued September 22, see
                            Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, September 24, 1944,
                            p. 328.</note> British and Dutch Embassies informed. [Haley.]</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>